description:
On November 23, 2022 SBF tweeted "I’ll be speaking with @andrewrsorkin at the @dealbook summit next Wednesday (11/30)." (https://twitter.com/SBF_FTX/status/1595512579417378837)

If Sam Bankman-Fried (SBF) physically appears at the New York Times (NYT) DealBook Summit, this market will resolve to "Yes". Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For the purposes of this market "physically appears" means that SBF appears on the premises of the conference in-person. Any telecommuting or streamed/prerecorded appearance at the conference will not be sufficient to resolve this market to "Yes"

If the NYT DealBook Summit is rescheduled to occur on any date up to December 14, 2022, this market may resolve normally according to the rules as-written. If the NYT DealBook Summit is rescheduled to a date after December 14, 2022, or is otherwise cancelled, this market will resolve to "No".

The primary resolution source for this market will be official information from the New York Times, however a consensus of credible reporting will be used.
